# 💻 COMMAND: sessions
Description: Manages active command-and-control (C2) connections. SuperSploit features a native, background-threaded raw TCP listener encrypted via TLS. 

Usage:
    sessions            - List all active background sessions.
    sessions -l         - List all active background sessions.
    sessions -i <ID>    - Interact with a specific session by its ID.

Background Listener Details:
    - Start the background listener manually: `set listener true`
    - Connections are caught securely via an ephemeral TLS certificate.
    - Stage 2 fileless payloads are automatically injected upon connection.
    - To return to SuperSploit while interacting with a session, type `bg` or `background`.